steps.description:
You'll need dinner, dessert, breakfast, snacks, and drinks. Try buying the food only a couple days before, so you won't eat it all! You can also go out to eat ice cream, dinner, or breakfast (but not all three!). Try picking food that isn't very different, something that everyone will probably like. Don't get, for example, fish or veggie burgers. You can, however, have a choice of regular or veggie burgers. So, always have something that everyone will want to eat. Below are some simple suggestions for all the food and drinks you'll need. But, you can also think of your own! Dinner: The most common dinner at a sleepover is pizza. This is a pretty safe choice, that most people like. If you're getting pizza, always have at least one plain and one with a topping. (pepperoni always works). Other dinner choices are chicken, pasta, hot dogs and hamburgers. Know what your friends like, but if you don't know, just get pizza. If you invited a friend who you know doesn't like pizza, make sure to have an alternative for them. Sometimes it is fun to cook the dinner entirely yourself, and although this takes time it can be a very rewarding experience. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/b8\/Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/b8\/Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Dessert: For dessert, be creative! A great idea is to make dessert at the party, like ice cream sundaes, cupcakes, or a cake. You can just decorate them or make them from scratch. Or, you can have a premade cake or brownies. It will save time if you want to do more activities. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/1b\/Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/1b\/Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet2.jpg\/v4-760px-Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Drinks: Always have water and soda. Ginger ale is always good to get, but to cover your bases, consider getting a variety such as cola, orange, root beer as well. Fruit juice is good, too. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0d\/Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet3.jpg\/v4-460px-Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0d\/Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet3.jpg\/v4-760px-Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Snacks: Of course you'll need snacks. Stock up on chips, pretzels, veggies with ranch or yogurt dip, popcorn, candy, fruit, and anything else that you can think of. Always have something healthy as an alternative. You do not have to eat nothing but junk food! {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0f\/Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet5.jpg\/v4-460px-Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0f\/Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet5.jpg\/v4-760px-Host-a-Tween-Sleepover-Step-2Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Breakfast: For breakfast, make your own waffles or pancakes. You could also ask a parent to make them. You can also have french toast sticks. Always have some delicious fruit, and orange juice and milk to drink.
